<!-- 
Info.plist Required Keys for Sweat2Scroll
Add these entries in Xcode: Target → Info → Custom iOS Target Properties
Or edit Info.plist directly.
-->

<!--
HEALTHKIT PRIVACY STRINGS (required by App Store review)
-->
<key>NSHealthShareUsageDescription</key>
<string>Sweat2Scroll reads your active calories, steps, weight, and height from Apple Health to compute your daily fitness goal. This data is processed entirely on your device and is never transmitted to third-party servers.</string>

<key>NSHealthUpdateUsageDescription</key>
<string>Sweat2Scroll does not write health data.</string>

<!--
CAMERA (for QR code pairing scan)
-->
<key>NSCameraUsageDescription</key>
<string>Sweat2Scroll uses the camera to scan your partner's QR code during the secure device pairing process.</string>

<!--
CLOUDKIT / PUSH NOTIFICATIONS (for tamper alerts and partner sync)
-->
<key>UIBackgroundModes</key>
<array>
    <string>fetch</string>
    <string>remote-notification</string>
    <string>processing</string>
</array>

<!--
APP GROUP (shared container between main app and extensions)
Must match: group.com.sweat2scroll.appblocker
Add in: Target → Signing & Capabilities → App Groups
Also add to ALL extension targets:
  - DeviceActivityMonitorExtension
  - ShieldConfigurationExtension
  - ShieldActionExtension
-->

<!--
ENTITLEMENTS FILE (Sweat2Scroll.entitlements)
Xcode auto-generates this when you add capabilities.
The following must be present:

com.apple.developer.family-controls              → Boolean: YES
  ⚠️  REQUIRES APPLE ENTITLEMENT APPROVAL
  Apply at: https://developer.apple.com/contact/request/family-controls-entitlement
  Testing WITHOUT this: use .individual authorization (already in AppEntry)

com.apple.developer.healthkit                   → Boolean: YES

com.apple.security.application-groups          → Array:
  group.com.sweat2scroll.appblocker

aps-environment                                 → String: development (then production)
  Required for CloudKit push notifications

iCloud                                          → Boolean: YES
  with CKSharingSupported: YES
-->

<!--
SWIFT PACKAGE MANAGER DEPENDENCIES
Add in Xcode: File → Add Package Dependencies

1. WasmKit (Wasm runtime for OPA policy execution)
   URL: https://github.com/swiftwasm/WasmKit
   Version: latest stable

2. No other external dependencies required.
   CloudKit, HealthKit, FamilyControls, ManagedSettings,
   DeviceActivity, CryptoKit are all Apple-native frameworks.
-->

